Heat your oven to 200°C. Pour the @water{300%ml}(for the rice) into a #saucepan{} over high heat. Stir in the @vegetable stock powder{1} and pour in the @basmati rice{150%g} and @ground turmeric{1%tsp}. Stir and bring to the boil, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice is cooking, halve the @bell pepper{1}, remove the core and the seeds then thinly slice. Trim the @carrot{1} then grate on the coarse side of your #grater{} (no need to peel), peel and grate the @ginger{1%thumb-sized piece}. Trim the @spring onion{2} then thinly slice. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}.

Pop the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{150%g} onto a #roasting tray{}, drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} over a medium high heat. Once hot, add the bell pepper. Stir-fry until the pepper has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the spring onions, ginger, lime zest, and a tiny pinch of @?chilli flakes{pinch} (you can add more later if you want to ramp up the heat!) into the pan with the pepper. Stir together and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @ketjap manis{25%ml} and the @soy sauce{25%ml}. Stir together and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Mix the coriander with the @sesame oil{24%ml} in a small #bowl{}. Squeeze in half the lime juice and a pinch of pepper and @sugar{pinch}. Mix together. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir it into the veggie mixture along with the grated carrot. Serve in #bowls{} with the herby drizzle on top and a sprinkle of peanuts. Scatter some @?red chilli flakes{} on top if you like things extra spicy! Enjoy!